author: Russell Brand
description:
Trump’s plan to deploy the National Guard into Washington, DC raises big questions about power, policing, and democracy. Is this about protecting communities, or about granting unprecedented authority to the state? I explore how measures like this can be justified one moment and weaponized the next—depending on who holds power—and why real safety must come from communities, not just force.
